modules.description: Reads data from a file descriptor into a buffer for parsing, using `Unix.read` to fill the buffer as needed. Works with `Unix.file_descr` and `Reparse.input` types. Useful for streaming input from files or sockets when implementing custom parsers.

This module provides streaming input handling for file descriptors using `Unix.read` to populate buffers during parsing. It works with `Unix.file_descr` and `Reparse.input`, enabling efficient, incremental data processing from files or sockets. You can use it to implement custom parsers that read from file descriptors, such as parsing network protocols or large files without loading the entire content into memory. For example, it can read HTTP headers line by line from a socket without preloading the full response.
